==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Boned
<hw>Boned</hw> <pr>(b⟦omac⟧nd)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having (such) bones; -- used in composition; <as>as,
big-<ex>boned</ex>; strong-<ex>boned</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>No big-<qex>boned</qex> men framed of the Cyclops' size.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Deprived of bones; <as>as, <ex>boned</ex> turkey or
codfish</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Manured with bone; <as>as, <ex>boned</ex>
land</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>bone-dry</ent>⟦br⟧
